SIMPLE: impropriety
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impropriety
<hw>Im`pro*pri"e*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Improprieties</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>improprietas</ets>; cf. F. <ets>impropri⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧</ets>.
See <er>Improper</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of being
improper; unfitness or unsuitableness to character, time place, or
circumstances; <as>as, <ex>impropriety</ex> of behavior or
manners</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is improper; an unsuitable or improper
act, or an inaccurate use of language.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But every language has likewise its <qex>improprieties</qex> and
absurdities.</q> <rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Many gross <qex>improprieties</qex>, however authorized by
practice, ought to be discarded.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Improsperity</ent>⟦br⟧
